WEBVTT

00:01.410 --> 00:07.478
25 years, 25 years.

00:09.361 --> 00:19.294
As we've been saying for the last few weeks, the undeniable, irrefutable message of 25 years is God is good.

00:19.374 --> 00:21.918
Period, hard stop.

00:22.659 --> 00:30.930
Now, the most profound example of the goodness of God is, of course, Jesus, the perfect

00:31.490 --> 00:45.125
never changing, ever dynamic, atoning sacrifice that facilitates the forgiveness of our sins through His death, burial, and resurrection.

00:46.846 --> 00:54.334
Jesus is the greatest example of God's goodness that there ever was or ever will be.

00:54.375 --> 01:01.362
And it also struck me that many times, I would say even most of the time,

01:02.530 --> 01:13.446
that God manifests His goodness in people through the people that He brings into our lives as an expression of His goodness.

01:15.910 --> 01:18.614
This weekend, we will celebrate 25 years.

01:18.634 --> 01:20.036
Some of us are celebrating right now.

01:22.620 --> 01:27.567
You know, as a matter of fact, if you're under the age of 18, let me say that.

01:28.188 --> 01:32.434
Would you do me a favor and help your parents put their noise maker little

01:32.898 --> 01:36.522
horned tutor thing up just for the next few minutes.

01:36.542 --> 01:38.864
We're only going to be here for about another hour and a half in this service.

01:38.884 --> 01:52.359
But the people is what I see and think about the most when I celebrate 25 years.

01:54.241 --> 01:57.484
I think about Julie's mom and dad who are here this weekend.

01:57.845 --> 01:59.186
They'll be in the next service.

01:59.490 --> 02:02.875
They were actually here at our first service on September the 7th, 1997.

02:04.837 --> 02:14.070
And they actually provided the flowers that we put on the welcoming table outside the cafeteria at Forest Trail that day.

02:14.932 --> 02:25.266
And when I think back to that first service, I can't help but think, you know, we were, to say we were rough around the edges is an expression of God's grace.

02:25.826 --> 02:27.047
We were rough around the edges.

02:27.127 --> 02:35.176
I think Julie's mom and dad, when they loaded up to drive back to Mississippi, honestly, should have taken Julie and the kids with them, but I'm glad they didn't.

02:37.319 --> 02:41.103
I think about my mom who was there 25 years ago that day.

02:41.123 --> 02:55.058
My mom was there 55 years ago, but my mom who raised three boys by herself and taught us to love God, to love His ways, who taught us unconditional love, who taught us a work ethic that just won't quit.

02:55.554 --> 02:57.376
She'll be here in the next service as well.

02:58.457 --> 03:07.245
I think about Lake Hills Church, the people.

03:07.265 --> 03:10.188
You have no idea how grateful Julie and I are for you.

03:11.469 --> 03:19.076
And of all of the things that you have done for us over the years, nothing is greater than the environment and the home that you provided for our kids.

03:20.437 --> 03:25.522
For our kids to now be adults who still love the church

03:26.338 --> 03:27.580
That's a reflection on you.

03:27.880 --> 03:39.697
You created an environment where they could grow up and be somewhat normal that they didn't, you know, become a PK pastor's kid cliche, but they love God and they love his house.

03:39.717 --> 03:40.398
They love his people.

03:40.418 --> 03:42.140
They're still committed to it.

03:42.701 --> 03:46.466
And so we owe you a massive, massive thanks for that.

03:48.269 --> 03:53.156
If it weren't for you, we wouldn't have our two bonus girls, Ali and Sylvia.

03:53.236 --> 03:54.738
Now Ali's husband will.

03:55.234 --> 03:58.259
I mean, our nest keeps getting repopulated.

03:58.579 --> 03:59.561
It's amazing.

04:00.582 --> 04:19.450
But just over and over and over the goodness of God and above and beyond all is Julie.

04:19.470 --> 04:24.498
What you have shouldered and worked and prayed

04:24.674 --> 04:32.787
and sweated and endured and put up with, just in me, deserves a horn toot of its own.

04:36.112 --> 04:37.495
I love you with everything I have.

04:44.165 --> 04:47.731
Julie says frequently that stubborn gets a bad rap.

04:51.157 --> 04:52.018
She lives that out.

04:53.506 --> 04:54.508
in so many ways.

04:57.533 --> 05:00.418
But she is stubborn in all of the best and most beautiful ways.

05:00.498 --> 05:08.752
She is relentless in her pursuit of Christ, relentless in her pursuit of me, holding my feet to the fire.

05:10.195 --> 05:15.604
She is the original fearless mom of our kids and Lake Hills Church.

05:15.624 --> 05:19.090
We would not be here without Julie Richard.

05:27.906 --> 05:28.587
So God's good.

05:29.809 --> 05:32.072
God is good.

05:34.055 --> 05:37.160
I remember when Emily was in high school, I want to say a junior.

05:37.400 --> 05:39.023
I'm not real sure about the date.

05:40.545 --> 05:47.075
When Emily was in high school, Julie and I were watching TV in our room one night and Emily came bounding into our room.

05:47.115 --> 05:51.542
That's where most of our great conversations happened with Emily, usually late at night.

05:52.684 --> 05:54.226
We had an old

05:54.466 --> 05:56.808
style slave bed that didn't have a foot board.

05:56.848 --> 06:06.117
When we bought a bed that has a foot board on it, Emily said this foot, because she would sit on the end of our bed and talk and talk and talk.

06:06.838 --> 06:10.902
And when we bought a bed that had a foot board on the end of it, she said, this is like barbed wire to my soul.

06:15.106 --> 06:22.994
But I remember one night in particular, Julie and I were watching TV and Emily came bounding into our room and she said, oh, by the way,

06:24.290 --> 06:27.915
96 on my algebra II test.

06:28.376 --> 06:29.257
What now?

06:32.903 --> 06:36.888
I remember thinking, I really did think this in the moment, I thought she is so much like her mother.

06:39.933 --> 06:46.322
But I mean, just that unbridled joy, that unbridled excitement of a job well done,

06:46.946 --> 06:48.688
that statement, what now?

06:48.748 --> 06:50.831
It kind of became a battle cry for our family.

06:50.851 --> 06:58.220
And even around the offices of Lake Hills Church for a while, instead of saying, what's up, or how you doing, what's going on, we would all kind of go, what now?

06:58.520 --> 06:59.722
Usually with the finger snap.

07:00.883 --> 07:15.762
And I think as this message series comes to a crescendo, as 25 years comes to a crescendo, it's actually the perfect question slash statement to say, what now?

07:16.738 --> 07:25.390
And so I want you to turn to your neighbor and with passion and the finger snap, go down and then up, say, what now?

07:28.535 --> 07:29.757
It's fun to say, isn't it?

07:30.558 --> 07:33.662
I promise you, you will say that again today before you put your head on the pillow.

07:35.785 --> 07:37.147
But what now?

07:38.449 --> 07:39.671
God, 25 years.

07:40.932 --> 07:42.034
But what now?

07:42.242 --> 07:43.704
Where do we go from here?

07:43.764 --> 07:47.229
And to answer that question, I want us to go to the book of first Peter today.

07:48.351 --> 07:52.778
First Peter, today's message has just two things to remember, two points.

07:52.798 --> 08:05.296
First Peter chapter two, verses two through six, the Bible says this, like newborn babies crave pure spiritual milk.

08:05.376 --> 08:09.022
So that by it, you may grow up in your salvation.

08:09.122 --> 08:11.986
Now that you have tasted that the Lord

08:12.226 --> 08:13.648
is good.

08:13.708 --> 08:36.276
As you come to Him, the living stone, rejected by humans but chosen by God and precious to Him, you also, like living stones, are being built into a spiritual house to be a holy priesthood, offering spiritual sacrifices acceptable to God through Jesus Christ.

08:37.016 --> 08:41.522
For in Scripture it says, see, I lay a stone in Zion.

08:42.434 --> 08:45.338
a chosen and precious cornerstone.

08:45.638 --> 08:51.506
And the one who trusts in him will never be put to shame.

08:52.808 --> 09:04.043
So when you think what now, as a part of the Lake Hills Church family, as a product and a participant in 25 years, if today is your first day, you're part of the first 25 years.

09:06.587 --> 09:08.429
I want you to think what now?

09:09.631 --> 09:11.954
And the first clue

09:13.122 --> 09:15.485
is right here in the very beginning of this passage I just read.

09:15.545 --> 09:28.380
Number one, like newborn babies crave pure spiritual milk so that by it you may grow up in your salvation.

09:29.181 --> 09:33.447
Turn to your neighbor and with a smile and grace in your heart.

09:34.508 --> 09:36.370
Tell your neighbor, grow up

09:39.746 --> 09:44.052
I can only imagine how desperately Julie wishes I was sitting beside her right now.

09:46.676 --> 09:49.541
But it says to crave spiritual milk like a baby.

09:49.581 --> 09:51.484
That doesn't mean that we're supposed to be a baby.

09:52.125 --> 10:01.018
But like a child craves a mother's milk, craves nourishment, cries without it.

10:01.258 --> 10:03.261
That's to be our attitude.

10:03.281 --> 10:07.267
That's to be our heart for spiritual milk.

10:07.287 --> 10:09.010
We are to hunger and to thirst

10:09.186 --> 10:15.254
after righteousness, after right connectedness with God and right living out into the world.

10:15.574 --> 10:17.416
We're to crave that and to grow up.

10:20.360 --> 10:24.465
You're not here to be a spiritual infant your whole life.

10:25.647 --> 10:29.431
If you're going to heaven, if you have committed your life to Christ, that's great.

10:30.573 --> 10:32.035
But don't just stop there.

10:32.615 --> 10:36.260
Grow up, mature in that faith.

10:37.201 --> 10:38.002
This is where

10:38.370 --> 10:41.813
We begin to ingest Scripture.

10:41.833 --> 10:52.204
We're not just memorizing stuff to memorize it or be able to dazzle our friends in Bible study, but we're actually taking in the Word of God and making it a part of our spiritual DNA.

10:52.724 --> 10:53.725
We ingest it.

10:53.765 --> 11:01.313
We spiritually and emotionally and relationally and psychologically metabolize the Word of God.

11:02.193 --> 11:04.315
It becomes a part of who we are.

11:04.336 --> 11:06.898
It becomes the energy and the fuel for our living.

11:08.162 --> 11:13.088
And we use scripture as our guide for right living.

11:14.269 --> 11:20.216
It's where prayer becomes just a part of who we are when the Bible says, pray without ceasing.

11:20.857 --> 11:24.341
It doesn't mean that we walk around with our eyes closed, holding a pulpit Bible.

11:24.441 --> 11:26.363
Father, right now I just look, please don't.

11:28.145 --> 11:35.634
But it does mean that we are in constant communication with the King of Kings and the Lord of Lords.

11:36.674 --> 11:48.212
that at the drop of a hat, because we have spent time with Him privately and quietly, we're no longer strangers with Him when we need Him immediately and desperately.

11:49.314 --> 11:51.517
And so we come back to that.

11:51.858 --> 12:00.872
It means that we've got friends, maybe one or two close, close friends that we rely on, we go to for Godly counsel.

12:01.834 --> 12:04.498
We say, this is what I'm thinking about doing.

12:04.610 --> 12:05.791
This is what I'm struggling with.

12:05.811 --> 12:08.534
I need you to pray with me and I need you to hold me accountable.

12:09.916 --> 12:11.898
That's growing up.

12:13.700 --> 12:20.187
It's where we begin to say more often than not, God not my will, but your will be done because I know your will is better than mine.

12:21.228 --> 12:23.430
That's a tough one.

12:23.450 --> 12:27.735
Because I still, I've been walking with Christ for a long time.

12:28.796 --> 12:31.859
I still like things my way.

12:32.079 --> 12:33.341
Anybody else like things your way?

12:33.381 --> 12:34.482
Can I just see a show of hands?

12:36.418 --> 12:39.682
but to say, God, not my will, but your will.

12:41.245 --> 12:45.851
Romans 12, too, you're good, pleasing, and perfect will.

12:47.713 --> 13:05.618
So we grow up, we grow up, but then it says not only are we growing up personally, it says Jesus is the perfect cornerstone, and everyone who follows Jesus is like

13:05.826 --> 13:07.548
a living stone.

13:07.588 --> 13:10.350
Isn't that a fascinating concept?

13:10.370 --> 13:12.773
Oh, a living stone.

13:13.674 --> 13:14.755
You're like a living stone.

13:14.855 --> 13:23.043
I'm like a living stone and together we're being built up into this holy dwelling place, the temple of God.

13:24.444 --> 13:25.885
You may be a corner piece.

13:26.906 --> 13:30.149
You may be a piece of trim.

13:30.189 --> 13:32.972
You may be the gold on the altar.

13:33.052 --> 13:34.994
I don't know.

13:35.202 --> 13:50.720
We're living stone, so we grow up personally, but then collectively and corporately, we build up, we build up the body of Christ for 25 years, Lake Hills Church.

13:50.740 --> 13:52.342
If you know it, please say it along with me.

13:52.743 --> 14:02.194
Our purpose, the reason we exist, you've probably heard this before, is to grow the community of Christ one life at a time.

14:03.170 --> 14:04.091
Now you've all heard it.

14:04.131 --> 14:05.794
Let's say it again together like we mean it.

14:06.074 --> 14:10.500
To grow the community of Christ, one life at a time.

14:10.560 --> 14:14.866
One living stone at a time.

14:14.966 --> 14:18.671
We build up the body of Christ.

14:19.933 --> 14:21.355
We lift him up.

14:21.455 --> 14:23.758
We build up his body.

14:25.160 --> 14:29.906
That's why it's so important that we check our tones, man, especially if you're on social media,

14:30.274 --> 14:31.235
That's fine.

14:31.676 --> 14:33.739
But make sure that you're building people up.

14:34.239 --> 14:35.581
You're not tearing people down.

14:36.563 --> 14:41.229
You're not participating as the world participates in that nonsense.

14:42.050 --> 14:43.532
We're building each other up.

14:44.213 --> 14:45.335
I want to inspire you.

14:45.355 --> 14:46.416
I want to challenge you.

14:46.456 --> 14:54.788
A lot of times people will say things like, I am just being a truth teller.

14:56.250 --> 14:59.154
I'm just telling you like it is because I love you.

14:59.426 --> 15:05.173
And sometimes that's true, but it's also true that sometimes you're just being a jerk.

15:06.054 --> 15:07.655
And I'm just telling you the truth.

15:11.219 --> 15:16.125
I've shared with y'all some teaching from John Stott along the way.

15:16.786 --> 15:27.538
John Stott said that love without truth is too soft, but truth without love is too hard.

15:28.770 --> 15:29.692
I want you to think about that.

15:30.753 --> 15:31.274
Love with that.

15:31.575 --> 15:33.759
If you love somebody, you tell them the truth.

15:34.660 --> 15:38.787
Listen, for 31 years, Julie has loved the dog out of me.

15:39.649 --> 15:41.372
She will tell me the truth.

15:42.514 --> 15:44.477
Yeah, you know, you should not wear that.

15:45.880 --> 15:49.586
Or, yeah, you should not have said that.

15:51.234 --> 15:51.635
It's funny.

15:51.695 --> 15:54.138
We do a debrief between services every Sunday morning.

15:54.158 --> 15:57.904
We go over the service and, you know, kind of make tweaks if something worked or didn't work.

15:57.944 --> 16:05.775
And the first thing I ask, the first part of the message, first part of that meeting is always anything in the message I need to say or do differently in the second one.

16:05.795 --> 16:08.679
If Julie is in that meeting, that section of the meeting goes longer.

16:11.183 --> 16:12.325
It's really, really odd.

16:16.190 --> 16:18.834
But I listen to her because I trust her.

16:20.258 --> 16:22.080
I listen to her because she's smarter than I am.

16:22.260 --> 16:26.505
I listen to her because I know she loves Christ more than she loves me.

16:27.026 --> 16:32.171
I know she wants what's best in God's economy for me and for you.

16:32.732 --> 16:41.022
So if I need to do something different, she's going to tell me the truth, but she has spent 31 years loving me.

16:42.904 --> 16:48.530
There have been some times where I wanted her to love me a little less.

16:48.674 --> 16:53.980
Love without truth is too soft, but truth without love is too hard.

16:56.763 --> 17:00.808
We have to be willing to build up.

17:02.970 --> 17:07.455
Acts chapter one, verse eight, Jesus is about to conclude his earthly ministry.

17:09.738 --> 17:16.786
And he says these words, but you will receive power when the Holy Spirit comes upon you and you

17:16.962 --> 17:28.216
will be my witnesses, telling people about me everywhere in Jerusalem, throughout Judea, in Samaria, and to the ends of the earth.

17:29.638 --> 17:36.726
To the ends of the earth, you will be his witness.

17:39.029 --> 17:46.098
You have the power of the Holy Spirit Christ follower, and you will be his witness.

17:46.818 --> 17:50.882
You will invite people to church just to come alongside.

17:51.603 --> 17:54.085
Go, hey, we want you to taste and see that he is good.

17:54.105 --> 17:57.529
I want to share with you what God's given to me.

17:58.650 --> 18:00.912
You don't have to be super religious about it.

18:00.932 --> 18:03.215
As a matter of fact, don't be super religious about it.

18:03.755 --> 18:04.596
Just be sincere.

18:06.818 --> 18:11.383
Build up the church one life at a time.

18:13.886 --> 18:14.386
Grow up.

18:16.866 --> 18:27.818
If you're not a part of a systematic, intentional Bible study with other followers of Christ, you're not growing up like you could.

18:27.878 --> 18:39.130
I love it when people say, especially men, about this time of year, we're heading into fall, temperature is plunged down into the upper 90s.

18:41.872 --> 18:43.314
And men will say, you know,

18:45.858 --> 18:50.143
church for me is in a deer blind.

18:50.183 --> 18:51.405
That's church for me.

18:51.585 --> 18:54.929
Listen, I have encountered God in a deer blind in some profound ways.

18:55.970 --> 18:56.651
It ain't church.

18:58.093 --> 19:01.257
Church is people.

19:01.277 --> 19:04.901
Church is communing with God and His people.

19:06.223 --> 19:08.165
That's church.

19:08.325 --> 19:11.389
Now, you can have a profound experience with God on your own.

19:11.409 --> 19:12.050
You should.

19:14.274 --> 19:20.462
But that profound experience is never designed to exist or grow in a vacuum.

19:21.263 --> 19:22.885
It always grows in community.

19:23.426 --> 19:25.708
That's where we grow, that's where we get better.

19:26.189 --> 19:28.131
Iron sharpens, iron.

19:30.054 --> 19:34.800
So man, we grow up, but then we grow up, not just so we look at all the things I know.

19:34.820 --> 19:40.747
I'm about to dazzle you with my Greek and Hebrew lexicon off the top of my head.

19:41.368 --> 19:42.930
That's fine if you know Greek and Hebrew.

19:45.186 --> 19:48.809
if you're using it to build up the body of Christ.

19:53.474 --> 19:55.255
What did God say through the Apostle Peter?

19:56.116 --> 20:02.522
First Peter chapter two, verse six, we read it a minute ago, see I lay a stone in Zion, that's Jesus.

20:02.542 --> 20:10.950
A chosen and precious cornerstone and the one who trusts in him will never be put to shame.

20:14.574 --> 20:14.994
You know,

20:17.346 --> 20:20.210
I told you at the very beginning, I wish I could do what Corey does.

20:21.271 --> 20:22.753
It's just so much fun to me.

20:24.876 --> 20:31.545
And other than not being able to sing or play guitar that well, I would be right there with him.

20:31.565 --> 20:39.656
But if I came out here on this stage and tried to do what he did, I would be put to sing.

20:39.997 --> 20:43.521
I would be, you'd be like, oh, oh, Mac, we invited friends today.

20:44.883 --> 20:46.866
No, no.

20:50.530 --> 20:58.742
But the one who trusts in Christ will never be put to shame.

21:00.224 --> 21:03.749
That means he will never leave you nor forsake you.

21:03.789 --> 21:07.815
That means he is always good.

21:07.835 --> 21:18.450
And if you've never tasted that goodness, if you've never experienced it, you might be asking, well, how do you know?

21:20.418 --> 21:27.445
I could point you to some evidence and I'd be happy to, but understand that ultimately it's a relationship.

21:29.167 --> 21:31.449
And like any relationship, it takes trust.

21:32.470 --> 21:34.212
There will be some unknown.

21:34.252 --> 21:40.678
If you waited until you knew everything about anybody you were in a relationship with, you would be very lonely.

21:44.642 --> 21:48.306
But you choose to trust based on track records.

21:51.138 --> 22:01.231
And Jesus' track record begins with the empty tomb, with the fact that he died on a cross for you, like he died on a cross for me.

22:04.355 --> 22:13.107
Becoming our sin and taking on himself the payment and the penalty of that sin, which is death, so that you don't have to.

22:16.532 --> 22:18.354
Well, how do you know that?

22:21.762 --> 22:29.690
The great theologian was asked one time, what's the most profound truth that you have ever studied in all of your years of scholarship?

22:32.372 --> 22:39.359
The theologian thought for a second and he said, the most profound truth I know is this.

22:42.682 --> 22:46.026
Jesus loves me, this I know.

22:48.028 --> 22:50.450
For the Bible tells me so.

22:52.482 --> 22:57.388
little ones to Him belong.

22:57.408 --> 23:01.132
I am weak, but He is strong.

23:07.820 --> 23:15.590
You can know as much as you can know anything else that He is good and that He loves you because the tomb is empty.

23:16.731 --> 23:22.418
He got up from the dead with the promise of a new life for anyone who would follow Him.

23:24.578 --> 23:29.644
If there is one message out of the life of Lake Hills Church, it is that.

23:30.585 --> 23:32.267
It is the good news of Jesus Christ.

23:34.870 --> 23:37.132
And I want to ask you, if you will, bow your heads for just a moment.

23:38.954 --> 23:45.642
If you're here today, maybe you came to see Cory Morrow, maybe you came because you saw Ferris Wheel in the parking lot.

23:46.903 --> 23:52.850
Whatever your reason for walking in the door is, if you are here and you've never stepped into a relationship with God, you've never

23:53.442 --> 23:55.124
to see that He is good.

23:55.164 --> 23:58.749
We want to give you the opportunity to do that just right now.

24:00.111 --> 24:03.856
To pray a prayer of beginning, a prayer of commitment.

24:07.120 --> 24:10.264
To walk into that relationship with Him.

24:11.225 --> 24:12.527
Just pray right where you're sitting.

24:13.869 --> 24:21.138
Something like this, just silently from your heart to God say this, just, Jesus, I need you.

24:24.482 --> 24:25.803
I confess my sin to you.

24:27.946 --> 24:36.255
I confess my sin holding nothing back in order to receive your forgiveness, your grace.

24:39.379 --> 24:42.703
And in this moment, I commit my life to you.

24:46.307 --> 24:49.410
Jesus, this is my what now moment with you.

24:49.450 --> 24:52.914
And I will follow you from this moment forward.

24:56.962 --> 24:59.306
I pray this prayer in your name.

25:05.896 --> 25:16.192
If that's your prayer, our privilege as a church is to tell you that this is the biggest moment of your life.

25:19.317 --> 25:24.946
And we wanna celebrate that with you, but we wanna just help with the moments that follow

25:26.146 --> 25:29.712
as you begin to grow up in this new faith.

25:32.596 --> 25:38.946
So if that was your prayer, just before we do anything else, would you just quietly raise your hand as our heads are bowed?

25:38.966 --> 25:48.962
Just raise your hand and hold it up high over your head for a moment as a statement physically of the commitment spiritually that you just made to Christ.

25:50.685 --> 25:53.810
And know that as a church family, we celebrate that moment with you.

25:57.794 --> 26:05.381
And our family tradition around here is, as you put your hands down, we're gonna put our hands together to tell you, welcome home.

26:06.264 --> 26:06.706
Welcome home.

